<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><channel><title>Manita Pote</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/</link><description>Recent content on Manita Pote</description><generator>Hugo -- 0.147.2</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 12 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://manitapote.github.io/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Coordinated Campaigns and Information Integrity During the 2023 Israel-Hamas War on Twitter</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper7/</link><pubDate>Sun, 12 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper7/</guid><description>This study uncovers how coordinated campaigns shaped the information environment on Twitter during the 2023 Israel-Hamas War, analyzing 4.5 million tweets across 11 coordinated groups using multimodal methods.</description></item><item><title>Coordinated Reply Attacks in Influence Operations: Characterization and Detection</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper5/</link><pubDate>Sat, 07 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper5/</guid><description>This study presents a framework to detect the user accounts involved in coordinated attack on targets based on replies/comments.</description></item><item><title>Labeled Datasets for Research on Information Operations</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper6/</link><pubDate>Sat, 07 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper6/</guid><description>This paper presents labeled datasets covering 26 information operation campaigns to support development and benchmarking of IO detection algorithms.</description></item><item><title>Location</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/location/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/location/</guid><description>Professor Dr von Igelfeld&amp;#39;s mailing and office addresses at the Institute of Romance Philology.</description></item><item><title>Office Hours</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/officehours/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/officehours/</guid><description>Schedule and location for Professor Dr von Igelfeld&amp;#39;s office hours.</description></item><item><title>Survey on Embedding Models for Knowledge Graph and its Applications</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper4/</link><pubDate>Sun, 14 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper4/</guid><description>A survey of knowledge graph embedding models covering translation-based and neural network-based approaches and their applications.</description></item><item><title>Computational Propaganda Theory and Bot Detection System: Critical Literature Review</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper3/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper3/</guid><description>A critical literature review of computational propaganda theory and bot detection systems on social media platforms.</description></item><item><title>How to Handle Extremely Imbalanced Datasets</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/blogs/imbalanced-dataset/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/blogs/imbalanced-dataset/</guid><description>A guide to undersampling techniques for handling imbalanced datasets, including prototype generation, prototype selection, and cleaning methods.</description></item><item><title>A Multi-Platform Collection of Social Media Posts about the 2022 U.S. Midterm Elections</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper2/</link><pubDate>Fri, 02 Jun 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper2/</guid><description>This paper introduces MEIU22, a multi-platform dataset of social media posts about the 2022 U.S. Midterm Elections spanning Twitter, Facebook, Instagram, Reddit, and 4chan.</description></item><item><title>Manipulating Twitter Through Deletions</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper1/</link><pubDate>Tue, 31 May 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/papers/paper1/</guid><description>Presents a method to estimate user deletion behavior on social media and investigates online manipulation tactics observed through deletion patterns, revealing coordinated inauthentic activity on Twitter.</description></item><item><title>List of Irregular Verbs Across Romance Languages</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/data/data1/</link><pubDate>Thu, 07 Mar 2013 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/data/data1/</guid><description>This dataset contains all irregular verbs in known Romance languages.</description></item><item><title>Lectures at the Villa of Reduced Circumstances</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/courses/course1/</link><pubDate>Mon, 10 Mar 2003 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/courses/course1/</guid><description>This graduate course presents classical results in Romance philology.</description></item><item><title>Portugese Irregular Verbs</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/books/book1/</link><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 1997 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/books/book1/</guid><description>This book discusses Portugese irregular verbs in great details.</description></item><item><title>Profanity in Early Irish</title><link>https://manitapote.github.io/courses/course2/</link><pubDate>Sat, 16 Jun 1990 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/courses/course2/</guid><description>This undergraduate course discusses profanity in Early Irish.</description></item><item><title/><link>https://manitapote.github.io/publications/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://manitapote.github.io/publications/</guid><description>&lt;!DOCTYPE html>
